1. landing page with a selection of random games on sale by default + nav bar to search for a specific game

2. user searches a game, this will utilize game lookup endpoint to find the specified query 

3. displays result: game + current and original prices + review scores + links to buy searched game

4. a form that allows users to specify a list of games to be displayed from the CheapShark API

5. form lets the user filter the results by review score, price, and if they are from a specific store

6. after inputs are given, script will run through CheapShark games array in a forEach loop, adding games which fall in with the specified filters

7. results display below the form in an <ol>, with each <li> displaying a result similar to the search result above